@node archive.contents " Archive Contents "

    THE VBD ARCHIVE
    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
      Normally your have the 'VBD' package with the following files...

    S      (dir)
      VBD.lea                            (VBD's Learn-File)
      VBD.configuration                  (VBD's Configuration)
      VBD.boot.spl                       (Sample Boot 'Ok')
      VBD.unknown.spl                    (Sample Boot 'Unknown')
      VBD.virus.spl                      (Sample 'Virus')

    Libs    (dir)
      reqtools.library

And the following
      Install                             (Installation script of VBD)
      Install.info
      VBD.English.doc                     (The doc in ASCII text)
      VBD.English.Guide                   (What you are reading now!!!)
      VBD_v2.6                            (VBD itself)
      VBD_v2.6.info                       (His icon!!! he he)
@endnode

@node knownbugs " Known Bugs "

               ************************************************
               **********                          ************
               **********         KNOWN BUGS       ************
               **********                          ************
               ************************************************


    ->   There can be some problems when  you save VBD's configuration file
         if you have a special Kickstart (ROM switcher).
         VBD's configuration file is not  compatible with older versions of
         the configuration file.

    ->   When VBD is iconified, and  when  the  CPU  is not free,you cannot
         open the main window (for example,  when you crunch something with
         Power Packer, it sets itself  a  task priority that doesn't permit
         VBD to run).

    ->   The 'Setpatch' for Workbench  v2.1  seems  to be incompatible with
         VBD.  It causes a 'Recoverable Alert' at beginning.
@endnode

